news.title: Madras HC orders probe, action on illegal sand mining
news.para: Petitioner P Balasubramanian owns a land parcel at Pudurpandiapuram village in Ottapidaram taluk. He alleged that one Murugesan had illegally encroached upon his property and started mining sand illegally.

news.title: Put construction permission details on board or face action: KDMC to developers
news.para: On this board, developers have been instructed to write all the information like building permission number, architect name, structural engineer, land details etc.

news.title: Use 13,000 acres of gram sabha land to boost infra in urban villages: Residents to DDA
news.para: Paras Tyagi of Centre for Youth, Culture, Law and Environment (CYCLE), an organisation working for public policy reforms in Delhi’s complex governance model with a special focus on villages, claimed that DDA commercially exploited the gram sabha land of villages in the past and the mistake shouldn’t be repeated.

news.title: UPPCB imposes Rs 27.5 crore fine on 70 brick kiln operators in Amroha dist
news.para: The move comes after they disregarded the orders of the National Green Tribunal (NGT) and ran their operation without the requisite No Objection Certificate (NOC) from the UPPCB.

news.title: Indore civic body identifies 2,500 property & water tax defaulters
news.para: “We have identified around 2500 defaulters, who have at least Rs 1 lakh or more due as property and water taxes. Of them, around 10 departments and establishments have about Rs 200 crore pending with them,” IMC additional commissioner Abhilash Mishra said.

news.title: Visakhapatnam civic body collects its highest ever property tax of Rs 306 crore in 2023
news.para: GVMC aims to get 500 crore through property tax in the 2023-24 fiscal. Officials said many taxpayers took advantage of the civic body’s ‘early bird’ offer in April, paying 120 crore with 5% tax rebate under the scheme.

news.title: Mapusa civic body to raise rent for shops
news.para: hairperson Priya Mishal said that the decision to revise the rent was taken as per the rent certificate received from PWD dated March 23, 2023.

news.title: Indore: Under-construction building razed for violating NGT norms
news.para: IMC team on Friday morning reached Triveni Nagar on complaints of resident welfare association about an illegal construction being made on a plot.

news.title: Kochi corporation issues 'demolition' notice to flat at Kaloor
news.para: As per the order, a seven-metre road on the northern side of the property is shown as the entry. However, the deed of Regal Flat builders shows that on the northern side ‘the remaining properties belong to the vendors.’

news.title: Mumbai: BMC slaps fine Rs 2 lakh each on two construction firms for causing pollution
news.para: ​​Show-cause notices were served to 603 construction sites and notices were issued to a total of 2,955 constructions for not following the guidelines during this period, it said in a release.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals over 2,600 properties over tax default
news.para: ​​The highest number of properties were sealed in the areas falling under the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation’s west zone.

news.title: Enforcement directorate attaches property of Bajwa Developers
news.para: The ED has attached assets under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act, 2002 (PMLA). Following registration of cases by Mohali police, the ED started its investigation.

news.title: No cover, no sprinkling: GRAP-3 bites the dust at construction sites in Gurugram
news.para: All construction, barring some public infrastructure and defence projects, has to stop when GRAP-3 is invoked to improve air quality.

news.title: Amitabh Bachchan leases four offices in Mumbai’s Andheri to Warner Music India
news.para: The tenant will be paying total rentals of over Rs 11 crore through the entire lease tenure. The lease will be operative starting from March 2024. ET had reported in September that Bachchan bought these four offices totalling over 12,000 sq ft built up and 10,800 sq ft carpet area for nearly Rs 29 crore.

news.title: ED attaches more assets of Kunal Builders & Developers who sold slum flats to celebrities
news.para: On Friday, the ED issued a press release stating that the attached properties included a residential flat on Victorian Anchor building at Parel and fixed deposit of Savla and his wife Jayshree.

news.title: Promoters of Kolte-Patil Developers sell stake worth Rs 111 crore
news.para: As per the bulk deal data available with the National Stock Exchange (NSE), Rajesh Anirudha Patil, Sunita Rajesh Patil and Sunita Milind Kolte offloaded more than 22.80 lakh equity shares, amounting to a 3 per cent stake in the company.

news.title: UK house prices fall in 2023, to stay subdued next year, says Nationwide
news.para: Britain's housing market, which enjoyed a boom during the COVID-19 pandemic, has been hit by higher borrowing costs after the Bank of England pushed up interest rates in its battle to tame inflation.

news.title: China: Guangzhou R&F's co-founder resigns as CEO
news.para: Earlier this year, 70-year old Zhang admitted bribing a former San Francisco official and entered into a deferred prosecution agreement with U.S. prosecutors to avoid criminal charges, according to a court filing.

news.title: Industry experts expects about 10% rise in property prices in 2024
news.para: Real estate stakeholders expects the momentum to continue in 2024 and are predicting a rise in real estate prices across segments.

news.title: Housing sales sees 31% growth in top seven cities in 2023: Anarock
news.para: New launches across the top seven cities saw a 25% annual rise – from approx. 3,57,640 units in 2022 to approx. 4,45,770 units in 2023. MMR and Pune saw the most new launches, together comprising an nearly 54% share of total new launches in the year.
